## 1) Download the latest Nvidia driver.

It is recommended you have the latest version of Nvidia/AMD Driver. Go ahead to the official website to download the driver. 

NVIDIA: https://www.nvidia.com/Download/index.aspx? \
AMD (ATI): https://www.amd.com/en/support \
Intel: https://downloadcenter.intel.com/

## 2) Download the latest Display Driver Uninstaller.

Now, go ahead and download the latest DDU from the official website.

Display Driver Unisntaller Official link: https://www.wagnardsoft.com/display-driver-uninstaller-ddu-

## 3) Run DDU for the first time.

Before you doing anything else, you need to setup DDU for the first time. You may need to skip this step if you've already done it once.

